      {
        "id": "multi_hop_qa",
        "title": "Beating the Multi-hop Benchmark",
        "content": "Key ideas:\n- MuSiQue\n- 2WikiMultiHopQA\n- 20% gain\n\nOn MuSiQue and 2WikiMultiHopQA, HippoRAG single-step retrieval matches iterative chain-of-thought retrieval (IRCoT) while costing 10-30× less by replacing repeated LLM calls with one PPR graph traversal.",
        "position": {
          "x": 7,
          "y": 6
        },
        "type": "text"
      },
      {
        "id": "hipporag_limits",
        "title": "What HippoRAG Can't Do Yet",
        "content": "Key ideas:\n- LLM extraction cost\n- dynamic updates\n\nBuilding the KG requires calling an LLM for OpenIE on every document, incurring upfront indexing cost; the paper also notes the index is static and does not yet support efficient online updates as corpora grow.",
        "position": {
          "x": 11,
          "y": 6
        },
        "type": "text"
      }
    ],
    "quiz": {
      "id": "quiz-stage-3",
      "question": "Which of these is a stated limitation of HippoRAG? Answer with a number.",
      "type": "multiple-choice",
